OL,7,FSonia began sobbing. After months of
OL,8,Fstaying strong for her grandchildren,
OL,9,Fholding it together, she had been
OL,10,Ftipped over the edge.
OL,12,FSonia was now in an impossible
OL,13,Fposition, and time was not on her side.
OL,15,F"I just fear for the children. It's
OL,16,Fnot fair on them," she says.
OL,18,F"They're beautiful children. They're
OL,19,Fliterally my life... they've been
OL,20,Fthrough so much trauma. I'm not going
OL,21,Fto put them through this."
